@node INTRODUCTION "Introduction"

                                   @{b}@{FG shine}Form2Text@{FG text}@{ub}

Anyone who has set up a form on a website without access to cgi-bin scripts
will know that the information you receive takes forever to reformat and read
because of the stupid format form data is mailed to you. This utility removes
this problem.

It is common for people without cgi-bin access to set the ACTION="" field of
the <FORM ...> tag to ACTION="mailto:<address>". This utility will convert
replies sent from such a form into plain text, ANSI text, html or Amigaguide.

@endnode
@node REQUIREMENTS "Requirements"

    While this has only been tested on my A1200 (030/882, 18Meg ram) it
should work on /any/ Amiga with no trouble.

@endnode
