@node USAGE "Usage"

    @{FG shine}NOTE WELL:@{FG text}

    Form2Text will only work correctly on files which contain ONLY the form
results, ie: no mail header or extraneous junk. JUST the results. This can be
easily done by saving the message from your mail program without the header.
For example:

    YAM: Select the form in the folder list and click on 'Read'. When the
         read window is displayed click on 'Save'. From the popup select
         the first part of the message (normally of type 'text/plain' or
         text/x-www-form-urlencoded (if not from an Amiga browser)) NOT
         'Original' or 'All Texts' and save it to a new file. This is the
         file you will process.


    Form2Text is used from a shell window. The parameters are:

    @{b}S=SOURCE/A@{ub}  Name of the file to process. Wlidcards ARE NOT
                supported in version 1.2. This file must contain ONLY the
                form reply.

    @{b}O=OUTPUT/K@{ub}  Name of the file to output the processed results to.
                If this is not specified then the output goes to a file who's
                name is the same as the source file plus a '.form' extension.
                eg: If the source is 'foo' the output is 'foo.form'

    @{b}M=MODE/N@{ub}    Output mode, defaults to Text.

                0 = Text.
                1 = ANSI. Field names are shown in pen 2.
                2 = HTML. The form is converted to a table:

                          <TABLE>
                          <TR><TD>Field name</TD><TD>Field Data</TD></TR>
                            etc
                          </TABLE>

                3 = Amigaguide. The form is converted to an Amigaguide
                    page:

                          node SOURCE "SOURCE"
                            {b}{FG shine}Field name{FG text}{ub} Field Data
                          endnode

    @{b}R=RECASE/S@{ub}  When set this ensures that the field name always
                begins with an uppercase letter while the rest of the name
                is lowercase. Eg: ADDRESS becomes Address. The field data
                is not affected.

    @{b}A=APPEND/S@{ub}  When set Form2Text will append the processed form to
                the output file rather than overwriting it.


    @{b}V=VERBOSE/S@{ub} When set Form2Text will display some information about the
                input file, output file and mode and it will display the
                field name and contents as it processes them.
@endnode
